                                    \addplot+[soliddot, red] coordinates {(3,-5)} node[right] {$(3,-5)$};
                                    \end{axis}
                            \end{tikzpicture}
                            ]]>
                        </latex-image-code>
                    </image>
        </figure>

        <p>The domain is <m>(-\infty,\infty)</m>. The graph of <m>f(x)</m> opens upward so the vertex is the minimum point. The <m>y</m>-value of <m>-5</m> is the minimum. The range is <m>[-5,\infty)</m>.</p>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>Identify the domain and range of <m>g(x)=-3(x+1)^2+6</m>.</p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <figure xml:id="figure-domain-and-range-from-vertex-form-2">
