                <statement>
                    <p>In a race, a car drove through the starting position at the speed of <m><var name="$v0"/></m> meters per second. It was accelerating at <m><var name="$acceleration"/></m> meters per second squared. Its distance from the starting position can be modeled by the function <m>d(t)=<var name="$func"/></m>. Answer the question with technology.</p>

                    <p>After <var name="$t1" width="10" /> seconds, the car was <m><var name="$d1"/></m> meters away from the starting position.</p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p>Use technology to graph the function <m>d(t)=<var name="$func"/></m> and <m>y=<var name="$d1"/></m>, and then find their intersection, <m>(<var name="$t1"/>,<var name="$d1"/>)</m>.</p>
                    <figure>
